The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Globsyn hungry for more buyouts

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Bikram Dasgupta in Calcutta on Friday. A Telegraph picture

 Calcutta, Oct. 20: Fresh from turning around Syner Log-In Systems, the Chennai-based banking and financial services outfit, which it had acquired in the beginning of the year, city-based Globsyn Technologies is zeroeing in on another company and is likely to seal the acquisition in the first quarter of 2007.

 Globsyn had picked up 41.49 per cent of Syner Log-In, a company listed on the BSE.

 Globsyn chairman Bikram Dasgupta said here today that the company was in talks with two Indian companies, of which talks with one were at an advanced stage. 

 Dasgupta said inorganic growth would help the company reach the Rs 100-crore turnover mark from its current turnover of Rs 35 crore to Rs 40 crore.

 The target company has a turnover twice that of Syner Log-In which recorded a turnover of Rs 12.69 crore in its financial year which is from July to June.

 Syner Log-In was set up by a family of technocrats from Chennai and has a staff of 300 to 350. The company specialises in banking and financial services software.

 Globsyn has turned around Syner Log-In. The company under Globsyn made a profit of Rs 2.88 crore in the last fiscal compared with a loss of s 83.45 lakh in the last fiscal. 




